@startuml pipeline_orchestrator
'──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
'  ACR-QA  v5.0.0rc2  —  Pipeline Orchestrator Detail
'  No swimlanes — single-column portrait-friendly activity diagram
'  King Salman International University  ·  CSE494  ·  2025-26
'──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName  "Arial"
skinparam defaultFontSize  10
skinparam shadowing        false

skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor        #E8EDF4
  BorderColor            #002654
  BorderThickness        2
  FontSize               10
  DiamondBackgroundColor #FFF3BF
  DiamondBorderColor     #C9A84C
}

skinparam arrow {
  Color     #002654
  FontColor #444444
  FontSize  9
  Thickness 1.5
}

skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFFDE7
  BorderColor     #C9A84C
  FontSize        9
}

title <color:#002654><b>ACR-QA v5.0.0rc2 — Pipeline Orchestrator (CORE/main.py)</b></color>

start

:⓪  Rate Limit Check  (Redis token bucket)
POST /v1/runs → 202 Accepted · run_id returned;

:①  Repository Ingestion
Validate path · detect languages · apply .acrqa.yml exclusions;

fork
  :Python tools
  Ruff · Bandit · Semgrep
  Vulture · Radon · jscpd · SCA;
fork again
  :JS / TS tools
  ESLint-security · Semgrep
  npm audit · jscpd;
fork again
  :Go tools
  gosec · staticcheck
  Semgrep;
fork again
  :Cross-language + IaC
  Secrets Detector
  IaC Scanner (28 IAC-* rules);
end fork

note right : ②  Parallel tool dispatch\n12 tools · thread pool · stdout captured per tool

:③a  Normalise → CanonicalFinding schema
config filter · scope exclusions (approx 15% eliminated before scoring);

:③b  Triage Memory Lookup
learned-suppression table · per-repo rules;

:③c  Cross-Tool Deduplication (2-pass)
location hash + rule hash · merge overlapping findings;

:③d  Intra-Procedural Taint Analysis (AST BFS)
confidence = max(0.4, 0.95 - 0.1*(h-1))  where h = hop depth;

:③e  Call-Graph Reachability (BFS, max_depth=5)
entry points: Flask/FastAPI routes · Celery tasks · __main__;

if (finding reachable?) then (yes)
else (no — unreachable / dead code)
  :Apply -20 confidence penalty
  retained for audit · deprioritised in ranking;
endif

:③f  Per-Rule Cap (max 5 per rule) + Sort by confidence descending;

:④  Five-Signal Confidence Scoring
severity (40%) · category (20%) · tool_reliability (15%)
rule_specificity (10%) · fix_validation (10%)
multi-tool bonus +5  →  Cs ∈ [0, 100];

if (Cs >= 30 ?) then (yes)
else (no — soft-suppress)
  :Mark deprioritised = True
  visible in dashboard, ranked last;
endif

:⑤  RAG Enrichment
dict_lookup(rule_id) O(1) from 66-rule KB (422 mappings)
→ Groq LLaMA-3.3-70B × 3 runs
N-gram entropy filter τ = 3.2 bits
store enrichment in llm_explanations (PostgreSQL provenance);

:⑤b  LLM-Augmented Detection + Second Opinion
LLMDetector: Groq scan at confidence threshold 0.75 (additive, not replacement)
Second Opinion: Ollama qwen2.5-coder:1.5b independent check
+15 confidence on agreement · -10 on disagreement;

:⑤c  Post-Quantum Attestation
ECDSA-P256 (classical) + CRYSTALS-Dilithium3 (NIST FIPS 204);

:⑥  Supply Chain Scan + CBoM
pip-audit · npm audit · CVE mapping (OSV offline ~1.5 GB)
62 cryptographic algorithms · NIST FIPS 203/204 PQC migration flags;

:⑦  Quality Gate Enforcement
evaluate .acrqa.yml severity thresholds → PASS / FAIL
FAIL: CRITICAL Cs>=70 · >5 HIGH · hardcoded secret Cs>=50
emit gate_result for CI/CD runner;

:⑧  Output Delivery
JSON · SARIF 2.1 · HTML · PDF
GitHub PR inline comments · check-run status
PostgreSQL: UPDATE run SET status=COMPLETED;

stop

legend top right
  |= Stage Group  |= Role                             |
  |<back:#E8EDF4>  ⓪–①  </back>| Rate limit + Ingestion         |
  |<back:#C8D8F0>  ②–③  </back>| Tool execution + Normalisation |
  |<back:#FFF3BF>  ④–⑤  </back>| Scoring + AI enrichment        |
  |<back:#D3F9D8>  ⑥–⑧  </back>| Supply chain + Gate + Output   |
end legend

@enduml
